sentence: Today's session closes with the NASDAQ Composite Index volume reaching the 10th place in the top ten list for this year.
The last time the index closed above 2.03 billion shares was on Jan 12 2017.
The total shares traded for the NASDAQ was over 2.07 billion.
Declining stocks led advancers by 1.4 to 1 ratio.
There were 1203 advancers and 1687 decliners for the day.
On the NASDAQ Stock Exchange 51 stocks reached a 52 week high and 26 reaching lows.
The most active, advancers, decliners, unusual volume and most active by dollar volume can be monitored intraday on the Most Active Stocks page.
The NASDAQ 100 index closed up .05% for the day; a total of 2.5 points.
QUALCOMM Incorporated ( QCOM ) had the largest percent change down (-12.72%) while CSX Corporation ( CSX ) had the largest percent change gain rising 3.74%.
The Dow Jones index closed down -.14% for the day; a total of -27.4 points.
General Electric Company ( GE ) had the largest percent change down (-2.55%) while Home Depot, Inc. (The) ( HD ) had the largest percent change gain rising 1.82%.
